    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "The superior adamantine-lead alloy known as keep stone is as highly prized as it is expensive, and for good reason: keep stone combines the Hardness and durability of the finest metal with inherent magical protection. Not only does the metal itself resist magical effects, but anyone in proximity to a large amount of it also enjoys a degree of protection from divination magic. Dwarven crafters have attempted to make this extra protection more portable and more affordable in the form of *keep stone amulets*. Each amulet is unique in its exact shape, size, thickness, and decorations, but typically, a *keep stone amulet* is roughly palm-sized and engraved with clan symbols, holy aphorisms, or a favorite line of poetry.   \n   \nWhile wearing a *keep stone amulet*, if you\u2019re the target of a spell with the detection or scrying trait, the caster must succeed at a DC 5 flat check or lose the spell.",
        "level": 19,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Rare",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
